| Governance       | Clear separation of concerns       |

---

# 12. Why Not Direct GraphQL Schema Exposure?

If full schema introspection is exposed:

* LLM may generate deep joins
* Internal fields become discoverable
* Renaming fields changes behavior
* Performance becomes unpredictable
* Query cost governance weakens
* Harder to cache and observe
* API contract collapses into DB structure

This approach may work in small prototypes.

It does not scale safely.

---

# 13. Strategic Framing

This design:

* Preserves architectural boundaries
* Enables rapid product evolution
* Keeps AI adaptable
* Maintains deterministic execution
* Protects performance SLAs
* Reduces long-term operational risk

It shifts extensibility from:

> GraphQL structure
> to
> Metadata governance

That is the central architectural decision.

